So let us sing something for her, and a little
present for her.

00:49:02.918 --> 00:49:04.824
May God bless.

00:49:05.204 --> 00:49:09.034
What a nice day to be here when it’s your
birthday.

00:49:10.594 --> 00:49:12.484
May God bless.

00:49:38.863 --> 00:49:46.188
Now last but not the least, very important
thing is that the senior people in Sahaja

00:49:46.178 --> 00:49:49.208
Yoga should not be called by their names.

00:49:49.238 --> 00:49:54.248
We can say Uncle or something Uncle Tom, is
to be done.

00:49:54.278 --> 00:50:01.688
It’s very important, and even I’ve heard
some Indian girls calling somebody: ‘John’.

00:50:01.739 --> 00:50:02.739
I said: ‘What?

00:50:02.748 --> 00:50:04.339
He’s like your father.

00:50:04.388 --> 00:50:06.429
How can you call like that?’

00:50:06.468 --> 00:50:08.029
‘Our husbands insist.’

00:50:08.018 --> 00:50:15.119
No, please, call them with some sort of a
uncle and aunty.

00:50:15.128 --> 00:50:19.208
Shouldn’t say like that, it’s not proper,
doesn’t look nice.

00:50:19.366 --> 00:50:23.908
Or address to elders always: ‘Sir’ is
a better idea.

00:50:23.916 --> 00:50:26.098
Shows you have some culture.

00:50:26.371 --> 00:50:28.456
We are not brats, first of all.

00:50:28.651 --> 00:50:33.536
And also we are not people who are hippies,
you see.

00:50:33.693 --> 00:50:35.931
We have to respect the elders.

00:50:36.211 --> 00:50:41.901
Very important, it is that we have to respect
all the elders, that are within you.

00:50:41.937 --> 00:50:44.781
That’s how you will be respected also.

00:50:45.097 --> 00:50:51.477
See to it that those ladies or gentlemen who
are senior people always call them by, either

00:50:51.518 --> 00:50:55.347
‘Mr’ or ‘Uncle’ or ‘Aunt’.

00:51:07.548 --> 00:51:13.748
He was all the time with Me but I somehow
or other sneaked out tying.

00:51:24.131 --> 00:51:25.349
Ah beautiful.

00:51:25.421 --> 00:51:27.309
Suits your hand very well.

